27static const int MAX_NEARBY_DISTANCE = 5;
28static const int MIN_ROWS_IN_BARCODE = 3;
29static const int MAX_ROWS_IN_BARCODE = 90;
30
31DetectionResultColumn::DetectionResultColumn(const BoundingBox& boundingBox, RowIndicator rowIndicator) :
32 _boundingBox(boundingBox),
33 _rowIndicator(rowIndicator)
34{
35 if (boundingBox.maxY() < boundingBox.minY()) {
36 throw std::invalid_argument("Invalid bounding box");
37 }
38 _codewords.resize(boundingBox.maxY() - boundingBox.minY() + 1);
39}
40
41Nullable<Codeword>
42DetectionResultColumn::codewordNearby(int imageRow) const
43{
44 int index = imageRowToCodewordIndex(imageRow);
45 if (_codewords[index] != nullptr) {
46 return _codewords[index];
47 }
48
49 for (int i = 1; i < MAX_NEARBY_DISTANCE; i++) {
50 int nearImageRow = imageRowToCodewordIndex(imageRow) - i;
51 if (nearImageRow >= 0) {
52 if (_codewords[nearImageRow] != nullptr) {
53 return _codewords[nearImageRow];
54 }
55 }
56 nearImageRow = imageRowToCodewordIndex(imageRow) + i;
57 if (nearImageRow < (int)_codewords.size()) {
58 if (_codewords[nearImageRow] != nullptr) {
59 return _codewords[nearImageRow];
60 }
61 }
62 }
63 return nullptr;
64}
65
66void
67DetectionResultColumn::setRowNumbers()
68{
69 for (auto& codeword : allCodewords()) {
70 if (codeword != nullptr) {
71 codeword.value().setRowNumberAsRowIndicatorColumn();
72 }
73 }
74}
75
76static void RemoveIncorrectCodewords(bool isLeft, std::vector<Nullable<Codeword>>& codewords, const BarcodeMetadata& barcodeMetadata)
77{
78 // Remove codewords which do not match the metadata
79 // TODO Maybe we should keep the incorrect codewords for the start and end positions?
80 for (auto& item : codewords) {
81 if (item == nullptr) {
82 continue;
83 }
84
85 const auto& codeword = item.value();
86
87 int rowIndicatorValue = codeword.value() % 30;
88 int codewordRowNumber = codeword.rowNumber();
89 if (codewordRowNumber > barcodeMetadata.rowCount()) {
90 item = nullptr;
91 continue;
92 }
93 if (!isLeft) {
94 codewordRowNumber += 2;
95 }
96 switch (codewordRowNumber % 3) {
97 case 0:
98 if (rowIndicatorValue * 3 + 1 != barcodeMetadata.rowCountUpperPart()) {
99 item = nullptr;
100 }
101 break;
102 case 1:
103 if (rowIndicatorValue / 3 != barcodeMetadata.errorCorrectionLevel() ||
104 rowIndicatorValue % 3 != barcodeMetadata.rowCountLowerPart()) {
105 item = nullptr;
106 }
107 break;
108 case 2:
109 if (rowIndicatorValue + 1 != barcodeMetadata.columnCount()) {
110 item = nullptr;
111 }
112 break;
113 }
114 }
115}

117// TODO implement properly
118// TODO maybe we should add missing codewords to store the correct row number to make
119// finding row numbers for other columns easier
120// use row height count to make detection of invalid row numbers more reliable
121void
122DetectionResultColumn::adjustCompleteIndicatorColumnRowNumbers(const BarcodeMetadata& barcodeMetadata)
123{
124 if (!isRowIndicator()) {
125 return;
126 }
127
128 auto& codewords = allCodewords();
129 setRowNumbers();
130 RemoveIncorrectCodewords(isLeftRowIndicator(), codewords, barcodeMetadata);
131 const auto& bb = boundingBox();
132 auto top = isLeftRowIndicator() ? bb.topLeft() : bb.topRight();
133 auto bottom = isLeftRowIndicator() ? bb.bottomLeft() : bb.bottomRight();
134 int firstRow = imageRowToCodewordIndex((int)top.value().y());
135 int lastRow = imageRowToCodewordIndex((int)bottom.value().y());
136 // We need to be careful using the average row height. Barcode could be skewed so that we have smaller and
137 // taller rows
138 //float averageRowHeight = (lastRow - firstRow) / (float)barcodeMetadata.rowCount();
139 int barcodeRow = -1;
140 int maxRowHeight = 1;
141 int currentRowHeight = 0;
142 for (int codewordsRow = firstRow; codewordsRow < lastRow; codewordsRow++) {
143 if (codewords[codewordsRow] == nullptr) {
144 continue;
145 }
146 Codeword codeword = codewords[codewordsRow];
147
148 // float expectedRowNumber = (codewordsRow - firstRow) / averageRowHeight;
149 // if (Math.abs(codeword.getRowNumber() - expectedRowNumber) > 2) {
150 // SimpleLog.log(LEVEL.WARNING,
151 // "Removing codeword, rowNumberSkew too high, codeword[" + codewordsRow + "]: Expected Row: " +
152 // expectedRowNumber + ", RealRow: " + codeword.getRowNumber() + ", value: " + codeword.getValue());
153 // codewords[codewordsRow] = null;
154 // }
155
156 int rowDifference = codeword.rowNumber() - barcodeRow;
157
158 // TODO improve handling with case where first row indicator doesn't start with 0
159
160 if (rowDifference == 0) {
161 currentRowHeight++;
162 }
163 else if (rowDifference == 1) {
164 maxRowHeight = std::max(maxRowHeight, currentRowHeight);
165 currentRowHeight = 1;
166 barcodeRow = codeword.rowNumber();
167 }
168 else if (rowDifference < 0 ||
169 codeword.rowNumber() >= barcodeMetadata.rowCount() ||
170 rowDifference > codewordsRow) {
171 codewords[codewordsRow] = nullptr;
172 }
173 else {
174 int checkedRows;
175 if (maxRowHeight > 2) {
176 checkedRows = (maxRowHeight - 2) * rowDifference;
177 }
178 else {
179 checkedRows = rowDifference;
180 }
181 bool closePreviousCodewordFound = checkedRows >= codewordsRow;
182 for (int i = 1; i <= checkedRows && !closePreviousCodewordFound; i++) {
183 // there must be (height * rowDifference) number of codewords missing. For now we assume height = 1.
184 // This should hopefully get rid of most problems already.
185 closePreviousCodewordFound = codewords[codewordsRow - i] != nullptr;
186 }
187 if (closePreviousCodewordFound) {
188 codewords[codewordsRow] = nullptr;
189 }
190 else {
191 barcodeRow = codeword.rowNumber();
192 currentRowHeight = 1;
193 }
194 }
195 }
196 //return static_cast<int>(averageRowHeight + 0.5);
197}

199// TODO maybe we should add missing codewords to store the correct row number to make
200// finding row numbers for other columns easier
201// use row height count to make detection of invalid row numbers more reliable
202void
203DetectionResultColumn::adjustIncompleteIndicatorColumnRowNumbers(const BarcodeMetadata& barcodeMetadata)
204{
205 if (!isRowIndicator()) {
206 return;
207 }
208
209 const auto& bb = boundingBox();
210 auto top = isLeftRowIndicator() ? bb.topLeft() : bb.topRight();
211 auto bottom = isLeftRowIndicator() ? bb.bottomLeft() : bb.bottomRight();
212 int firstRow = imageRowToCodewordIndex((int)top.value().y());
213 int lastRow = imageRowToCodewordIndex((int)bottom.value().y());
214 //float averageRowHeight = (lastRow - firstRow) / (float)barcodeMetadata.rowCount();
215 auto& codewords = allCodewords();
216 int barcodeRow = -1;
217 int maxRowHeight = 1;
218 int currentRowHeight = 0;
219 for (int codewordsRow = firstRow; codewordsRow < lastRow; codewordsRow++) {
220 if (codewords[codewordsRow] == nullptr) {
221 continue;
222 }
223 auto& item = codewords[codewordsRow];
224
225 auto& codeword = item.value();
226 codeword.setRowNumberAsRowIndicatorColumn();
227
228 int rowDifference = codeword.rowNumber() - barcodeRow;
229
230 // TODO improve handling with case where first row indicator doesn't start with 0
231
232 if (rowDifference == 0) {
233 currentRowHeight++;
234 }
235 else if (rowDifference == 1) {
236 maxRowHeight = std::max(maxRowHeight, currentRowHeight);
237 currentRowHeight = 1;
238 barcodeRow = codeword.rowNumber();
239 }
240 else if (codeword.rowNumber() >= barcodeMetadata.rowCount()) {
241 item = nullptr;
242 }
243 else {
244 barcodeRow = codeword.rowNumber();
245 currentRowHeight = 1;
246 }
247 }
248 //return static_cast<int>(averageRowHeight + 0.5);
249}

251// This is example of bad design, a getter should not modify object's state
252bool
253DetectionResultColumn::getRowHeights(std::vector<int>& result)
254{
255 BarcodeMetadata barcodeMetadata;
256 if (!getBarcodeMetadata(barcodeMetadata)) {
257 return false;
258 }
259
260 adjustIncompleteIndicatorColumnRowNumbers(barcodeMetadata);
261 result.resize(barcodeMetadata.rowCount());
262 for (auto& item : allCodewords()) {
263 if (item != nullptr) {
264 size_t rowNumber = item.value().rowNumber();
265 if (rowNumber >= result.size()) {
266 // We have more rows than the barcode metadata allows for, ignore them.
267 continue;
268 }
269 result[rowNumber]++;
270 } // else throw exception?
271 }
272 return true;
273}

276// This is example of bad design, a getter should not modify object's state
277bool
278DetectionResultColumn::getBarcodeMetadata(BarcodeMetadata& result)
279{
280 if (!isRowIndicator()) {
281 return false;
282 }
283
284 auto& codewords = allCodewords();
285 BarcodeValue barcodeColumnCount;
286 BarcodeValue barcodeRowCountUpperPart;
287 BarcodeValue barcodeRowCountLowerPart;
288 BarcodeValue barcodeECLevel;
289 for (auto& item : codewords) {
290 if (item == nullptr) {
291 continue;
292 }
293 auto& codeword = item.value();
294 codeword.setRowNumberAsRowIndicatorColumn();
295 int rowIndicatorValue = codeword.value() % 30;
296 int codewordRowNumber = codeword.rowNumber();
297 if (!isLeftRowIndicator()) {
298 codewordRowNumber += 2;
299 }
300 switch (codewordRowNumber % 3) {
301 case 0:
302 barcodeRowCountUpperPart.setValue(rowIndicatorValue * 3 + 1);
303 break;
304 case 1:
305 barcodeECLevel.setValue(rowIndicatorValue / 3);
306 barcodeRowCountLowerPart.setValue(rowIndicatorValue % 3);
307 break;
308 case 2:
309 barcodeColumnCount.setValue(rowIndicatorValue + 1);
310 break;
311 }
312 }
313 // Maybe we should check if we have ambiguous values?
314 auto cc = barcodeColumnCount.value();
315 auto rcu = barcodeRowCountUpperPart.value();
316 auto rcl = barcodeRowCountLowerPart.value();
317 auto ec = barcodeECLevel.value();
318 if (cc.empty() || rcu.empty() || rcl.empty() || ec.empty() || cc[0] < 1 || rcu[0] + rcl[0] < MIN_ROWS_IN_BARCODE || rcu[0] + rcl[0] > MAX_ROWS_IN_BARCODE) {
319 return false;
320 }
321 result = { cc[0], rcu[0], rcl[0], ec[0] };
322 RemoveIncorrectCodewords(isLeftRowIndicator(), codewords, result);
323 return true;
324}
